Description: Layer 4 Communications, Inc was grown internally as a division of Layer Four Solutions LLC.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: "Layer 4 Communications, Inc was grown internally as a division of Layer Four Solutions LLC and launched as a standalone business in 2012 to independently develop voice communications services. Layer Four Solutions was founded in February 2009 to provide Internet Service throughout Chicago. Today Layer 4 benefits from the established infrastructure and business services support of Layer Four Solutions while maintaining independence for product design and development decisions.  We believe that business phone systems today consist of the following three elements; Core functionality, legacy features and useful applications. Core functions, like calling, voicemail, transfer, hold, etc. are essential, they must be 100% reliable and a carrier will be judged against the competition based on their quality. Legacy features are those that only exist because they always have. They are holdovers from bygone technology and most people don’t need them. They are only used because of tradition. Useful applications are those that create real value for the user. These are the features that set a provider apart from the pack, but unless these features are simple, intuitive and convenient they might as well not even exist. We leverage our proven platform and drop the burden of legacy features and built upon it a new communications platform that adapts to our users because we don’t believe users should need to adapt their business to the way their phones work.  Until now VoIP services have focused on replicating traditional phone systems so closely that most have built in the same frustrations customers are trying to avoid. Rather than try to simulate analog technology in a new package, we are building the next generation of hosted voice services. The number of deployed hosted business Voice over IP seats are estimated to double between 2012 and 2016. With no clearly established market leader in the industry today Layer 4 is in a unique position to dominate the emerging market."

Full Description: V1 provides a unique model for innovation to the enterprise. We create an outsourced multidisciplinary innovation team that can strategize, ideate, prototype, market test, incubate and launch new business lines. We drive companies forward faster by leveraging lean and agile business methodologies that have long been used by Silicon Valley startups since Apple Computer was founded in the iconic Palo Alto garage. V1 is a hub for imagining, strategizing and building businesses. Founded by serial entrepreneur Cyrus Radfar, the founding engineer of AddThis, which was sold to Oracle in 2016, V1 inspires and advises companies that require new solutions to grow and diversify their risk. V1 works with existing companies to create new business lines which, once established, can be integrated back into the parent company.   We’ve developed a formula for helping shape new, scalable businesses. We work with companies to identify their strengths and learn from their weaknesses, with an eye toward helping them keep their competitive edge. V1 currently focuses on partners in the insurance, financial services, energy, raw materials, transport, manufacturing and media industries.   In terms of education, V1 offers curriculum to new and existing innovation groups to help keep them cutting edge. V1 can also guide corporate development teams through the transitions associated with making an acquisition, including helping support a buyer’s technical and business infrastructure as the target company’s team shifts and reshapes.   V1 is creating a community around ideas and a culture that cultivates them into scalable businesses. We’re looking forward to you helping us make it even better. Everyone that we work with and partner with is required to share our values.  We believe: - Take action: To build tomorrow, you must take a step today.  - Be fearless: The only true failure is the failure to learn. - Create space for yourself: A healthy mind and body drive powerful ideas. - Create space for others: We are defined by who we help. - Don’t compete—transcend: We live in a world of abundance, not scarcity.  - The status quo isn’t final: Dogma arises from fear and insecurity. - Listen more: Empathy is a muscle that requires exercise. - Perspectives polish new ideas: Inclusion creates a larger creative canvas.

Description: Pearson’s Clinical Assessment group offers innovative and comprehensive products and services to meet our varied customers’ needs.
Full Description: With more than 80 years of experience in the assessment field, Pearson’s Clinical Assessment group offers innovative and comprehensive products and services to meet their varied customers’ needs.  They are proud of their leadership role in assessment and the continuous timeline of many innovations.  Every day theyconcentrate on merging innovation with quality test design to develop increasingly more effective tools for children and adults, educators and clinicians. Clinical Assessment’s internationally recognized products and services assist skilled, compassionate professionals to improve lives.  For the U.S. market, they have a comprehensive portfolio of research-based instruments that are valid, reliable and represent the highest technical quality in assessments today.  They are particularly noted for their gold-standard assessment contributions in cognitive/ability, memory, neuropsychology, behavior, personality/psychopathology, achievement and speech/language.  Noted brands include the Wechsler and Kaufman families of products, MMPI, BASC, OLSAT, CELF, and PLS. Liqpay.com online payment system created by Siteheart lets anyone safely send money using mobile phone and Internet all over the world. Liqpay is based on one-time password technology (OTP), which guarantees strong identification of sender, card fraud prevention and the highest level of security. Another cornerstone of Liqpay is person-to-person card-to-card money transfer technology ("P2P"), provided by international payment systems Visa and MasterCard worldwide for any Issuing Bank, which lets recipient withdraw money from Liqpay system directly to the payment card of any bank worldwide. Liqpay.com developed the engine which allows exchange money using only the mobile phone number linked to Liqpay virtual account. Mobile phone number=Liqpay's user ID.  Deepmemo.com is a social quotation service, which makes it easy and quickly to save, manage and share information online (quotes, pieces of text and/or pictures).  The idea of Deepmemo is that as long as people read the web, they have necessity to save interesting links, texts, pictures, quotes and then discuss it and share with friends. Deepmemo web-site has web 2.0 and social network functionality: user profiles, tags, blogs, communities, friends, RSS feeds etc. Deepmemo service is useful for active Internet surfers, who'd like to remember interesting quotes or create their own collection of quotes for later usage. It's useful for journalists, bloggers, copywriters, and people, who work with texts, since Deepmemo can help find interesting quotes. Service can be of great help for students, scholars and scientists, who write a diploma or a thesis and often need a way to organize quotes. Deepmemo saves quotes with a link to original web-site and a screen shot, so it's a comfortable way to create bibliography. Advertising banners will be displayed in this block. Blogger can himself set a price for advertising in his blog and receive money directly to his payment card. FolkAd.com easily links bloggers and advertisers and provides easy way of payments to each other. This is NOT banner exchange network, NOT context advertizing, but POINT, site-targeted, P2P — advertizing service.
